-- Eramet, Michelin, Sanofi, Trigano, Valeo: French Equity Preview
-- B y   L a u r e n c e   F r o s t   a n d   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 2010-09-28T06:30:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/eramet-sanofi-trigano-valeo-french-equity-preview.html
France’s  CAC 40 Index  fell 16.32,
or 0.4 percent, to 3,766.16.  The SBF 120 Index  also declined 0.4
percent.  The following shares rose or fell in Paris. Stock symbols
are in parentheses.  Eramet SA  (ERA FP): Gabon’s President  Ali Bongo Ondimba 
said his government is still in talks over the size of the stake
it plans to take in the French nickel producer. The shares rose
1.4 percent to 218.85 euros.  Le Belier SA  (BELI FP): The aluminum aerospace and
automotive parts maker said it sees “sustained” sales growth
this year after posting first-half net income of 5.1 million
euros, up from a 2 million-euro loss a year earlier. The shares
added 0.6 percent to 6.32 euros.  Michelin & Cie.  (ML FP): The company launched a 1.2 billion
euros rights offer at 45 euros a share, according to a statement
on PRL newswire. The shares lost 0.7 percent to 65.26 euros.  Sanofi-Aventis SA  (SAN FP): The drugmaker agreed to buy
VaxDesign, a closely held U.S. biotechnology company, for as
much as $60 million. The shares fell 1.2 percent to 50.01 euros.  Trigano SA  (TRI FP): The maker of recreational vehicles
said full-year revenue rose to 698.1 million euros from 636.2
million euros. The shares advanced 4.8 percent to 17.75 euros.  Valeo SA  (FR FP): The auto-parts maker denied a report by
Wansquare that it is preparing a link-up with an unidentified
rival. The shares gained 0.5 percent to 33.34 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
